cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about sentence matching, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new architecture for the task, which involves the use of recurrent neural networks and attention mechanisms, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of autoencoders, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper proposes a new architecture that achieves state-of-the-art performance, indicating that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
